ain/FaceHeelTurn">Face&#150;Heel Turn</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Rosa, by going to the police and betraying Pantaleone.</span> Depending on who you show as the "good" and "bad" side, respectively.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeKnowsTooMuch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeKnowsTooMuch">He Knows Too Much</a>: Ruggero and Augusto Dallamano<ul><li> Leonardo Mori</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HiddenDepths" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HiddenDepths">Hidden Depths</a>: Fundling, natch.<ul><li> Also Signora Raffaela Falchi. Who would have thought that the respectable teacher was a rock musician's girlfriend and knows full well how to wield a gun?</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HideTheEvidence" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HideTheEvidence">Hide the Evidence</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Gaia Carnevare hid the evidence of Cesare's betrayal in her paintings.</span><ul><li> The secret room in the bulding <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">that was once the Dallamano manor.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HideYourLesbians" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HideYourLesbians">Hide Your Lesbians</a>: That <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Zoe and Lilia</span> were lovers is only revealed pages before <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Lilia is killed by Cesare Carnevare</span>. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustifiedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustifiedTrope">Justified</a> because the conservatively Catholic South Italians and especially <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"